The top 4 tips and tricks that I’ve learned over the years that have helped my hair thrive:

1) Wash LESS! Yes - you can train your hair to go longer in between washes. Over washing dries out both your hair and scalp. Start by pushing your wash day back 1 extra day, and make dry shampoo your new best friend! I used to wash every 3-4 days; I can now push it to 8-10 days. 

2) Double shampoo your hair when washing, focusing on the roots & scalp. Shampooing your hair twice gives you a proper cleanse, helping you better clean your hair and scalp while enabling your products to work more effectively. Focusing on shampooing the scalp versus the middle/ends prevents your hair from breaking and becoming too dry. 

3) Use a heat protectant. While wet, apply a heat protectant cream or spray to hair prior to drying and using heat tools to help protect your hair and avoid damage, split ends, etc. 

4) Brush your scalp day & night. This helps remove buildup and stimulates the hair follicles. Go through your entire scalp, deep brushing in sections with a few strokes. The brushing also helps to bring your scalp’s natural oils down through to the rest of your hair!

I’m always looking for new recipes to try out, as I tend to make the same things on repeat. I came across this ‘Marry Me Chicken’ the other night, and it was a winner! [ad]

• Marry Me Chicken •

Ingredients

- 3 large chicken breasts (sliced into cutlets)
- 1/2 tsp of @herbamare_canada 
- 1/4 tsp of ground pepper
- 6 tbsps of all purpose flour
- 2 tbsps of olive oil 
- 2 tbsps of unsalted butter 
- 3 cloves of minced garlic
- 1 cup of chicken stock
- 1 cup of heavy cream
- 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese
- 1/4 tsp of oregano 
- 1/4 tsp of thyme
- 1 tbsp of fresh basil 

Optional:
- 1 cup of sliced mushrooms
- 1/3 cup of sundried tomatoes 

Instructions 

1) Season the chicken with @herbamare_canada and pepper, then coat in flour and shake off excess.

2) In a large skillet, heat oil and melt the butter on medium. Swirl to mix oil and butter together evenly. 

3) Brown the chicken for 4-5 minutes each side or until golden brown and cooked through. Transfer onto plate, cover and set aside.

4) Sauté garlic until fragrant. Add chicken stock. Adjust the heat to medium-low and add in heavy cream and Parmesan cheese. Allow sauce to simmer for a few minutes, then season with thyme and oregano. 

5) Season with @herbamare_canada and pepper to taste, add in sundried tomatoes and cooked mushrooms, and then add chicken into the sauce to simmer and thicken. 

6) Garnish with fresh basil and serve over cooked pasta or rice! (I choose to serve it with potatoes).

Enjoy!
